# IP Addressing

## What is an IP Address?

An IP address is a unique identifier assigned to a device on a network.

Example:
192.168.1.10

## Types

- Public IP
- Private IP

## Private IP Ranges

10.0.0.0/8

172.16.0.0 - 172.31.255.255

192.168.0.0/16

## Key Learnings

- Every device needs an IP address
- IP addresses identify devices
- Routers use IP addresses to forward packets
